Description: Terracotta figure or lamp fragment, depicting a wing of a bird, Nike or Eros. Mould-made and hollow. Orange-brown Nile silt.
Curator's comments: Wing off a winged Nike, such as that found in Naukratis, currently in Cambridge, Museum of Classical Archaeology ( NA512) dated 3rd to 2nd century BC. Alternatively off an Eros such as that found at Naukratis and in the British Museum (GR 1888,0601.125). Alternatively this may be off a mould made lamp, though this seems less likely.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (KD.075) (Phase 1)
